description.narrative: UNICEF continued with its pivotal role in supporting the Ministry of Health, line ministries and partners in promoting positive behavioral practices towards mitigating and preventing diseases and other emergencies across the country. UNICEF C4D leading Risk Communication and Community Engagement (RCCE), implemented key interventions in 2021 which include COVID-19 vaccines roll out, Polio outbreak response, malnutrition prevention in six food insecure areas, flood response and safe reopening of schools. ;UNICEF supported partners with its evidence-based communication and community engagement programming reaching 7,579,988 people with integrated lifesaving messages, promoting demand for services and creating an enabling environment to address social norms. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:11/01/2022
